review.name: nice ice cave - not far from Seattle
review.reviewBody:
its a moderate trail that runs for 3-4 km each side. In the end 4 nice ice caves. It's not georgious but surely worth seeing if you have spare hours to spend. Trail is moderate. Recommend to take trail shoes as ice is very slippery.
Take some warm clothes when inside the small cave

review.name: Worst communication EVER
review.reviewBody: There was zero communication and now I’m stuck in a van with 50 people and couldn’t even sit with my kid. SOS.

Seattle City Tour

The Jade City Seattle is the largest city in the northwestern United States, the 15th largest metropolitan area in the United States, and is considered to be the fastest growing major city in the United States, located in Evergreen - Washington.

review.name: Mono Rail services in Seattle, wa
review.reviewBody:
Mono Rail services, which is unique in its distinct features of running on single track from Seattle Space Needle Centre to one of the oldest Pikes Market of Seattle and vice versa. Travellers purchasing tickets worth $6(For young people 18-64 age 
group) may enjoy round trip to its both connected stations. We family 
members, utilising its another special feature, after reaching to the Pikes Market, another end of the Space Needle Centre, we enjoyed Market places. We also had a walk to the costal area of the Seattle Port, situated on the Pacific Ocean. While returning to station back we had a cup of Expresso Coffee from the oldest counter of the Starbucks Coffee shop.As expecteded the taste of the Expresso Coffee was not as tasty as expected.It's also may be a reason that we are not accustomed with the method of mixing cream and other supplements in proper proportions, which may resulted in bad taste. 
   We after walking away from the ups and downs of the streets of the famous Pikes Market and surroundings we reached back to the Pikes Market Mono Rail station and enjoyed ride back to the Space Needle Centre. No, doubt  the Seattle Space Needle Centre is a most exciting sample of the distinct structure of the Architecture at the heart of the Seattle City. It was came to know that this structure has been carved on the Canada's pattern. People were discussing that in every city of Canada such types of raised structures are the place of attraction for the tourists. Near the Space Needle Centre homeless people were attracted as a band party playing musical instruments and dancing on music. Though, they entertained up to extent with their ultimate motive to get tips for their livelihood.Finally came back to our rresidence.
        The Mono Rail round trip remained a pleasourous ride.

review.name: very good tour
review.reviewBody: started in china town covered downtown . market  .parks. space needle then onto boeing museum excellent

itemListElement.name: Snoqualmie Falls & Leavenworth German Town Tour From Seattle

name: Snoqualmie Falls & Leavenworth German Town Tour From Seattle
description:
[Snoqualmie Falls] is one of the top ten waterfalls in the United States, whose name comes from the Indian language, meaning the moon, which has a supreme position in the hearts of the local Indians.

[German town – Levinworth] is the most famous German town in the northwest of the United States. The whole town is full of Burgosian style in southern Germany. 

The German town hosts 13 large-scale events each year, one of the most famous tourist destinations in Washington.

Visit Snoqualmie Falls before going to the Leavenworth German Town. Enjoy the lovely and sweet atmosphere of this popular small town.

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The service fee should pay to the tour guide in cash.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

review.name: poor tour
review.reviewBody: The falls were average and the shop was closed, we had to leave before it opened the tour guide  was not willing to wait, 15 minuets till it opened, German town was great lively and lots to see, my biggest complaint was the tour guide uninformative, spoke poor English, his bus was filthy dust on window surrounds, dirty windows, so taking photos was near impossible,then did not request, but insisted a gratuity of $10, by far the worst trip, of my 4 week stay in US

review.name: Bus ride Hell
review.reviewBody:
The place where the bus picked us up was the doorway of a restaurant. Every business in the area was closed including the restaurant. This was a hint of things to come.
The driver was horrible. I have video of him on his phone while driving down the highway. According to the GPS in my phone he drove (traffic permitting) 5 to 15mph OVER the speed limit the entire trip, in the rain and on mountain roads. Several times I felt the tires "Slip". Twice he violently swerved to avoid hitting a vehicle in the lane he was trying to merge into. He went left of center over a double yellow line and off the right onto the berm so many times I lost count. Leaving Seattle the rear A/C was so cold people where bundled up in their coats and he never asked if we were comfortable. During our return trip he could not get the rear A/C to work and we were hot all the way back. The topper was the van was filthy. The windows were dirty. The floor was dirty. The ashtrays were full of trash.
I would only recommend this trip as a gift to someone you hate and never want to see again.

review.name: Very disappointing
review.reviewBody:
We booked this trip in advance and thought “How bad can it be, since they are only offering transportation?”  It is bad. I don’t know about you, but when I am on vacation I want to take pictures of the area. We had to go to China Town for our pick up. The pick up
Spot was filthy, no businesses were open, the buildings were sprayed with gang graffiti and the driver pulled up, an ounces Leavenworth? Get in.  No Hello, how are, nothing. I think he wanted to get out of the neighborhood as bad as we all did.  The van was dirty, the inside of the windows were sticky from fingerprints, the ashtrays were full of past passengers wrappers, the floors had food particles in the seat legs. The driver did a slight explanation of the trip, gave us a verbal list of don’t do this, and drove so erratically and fast that even my husband was concerned over the drivers ability. Then we were forced to pay a $10 per person “service fee” aka tip. 
The Falls, nice area, but when we arrived for our 15 minute stop, the gift shop and museum were closed.  Thank goodness the restroom was open because we wouldn’t be stopping for another 2 hours. 
The Bavarian Village is disappointing. If you have ever been to Germany you will be disappointed. But if you like Italian, Mongolian and Americanized Bavarian food you will not be disappointed. The shops made me feel like I was at a flea market although there were a couple nice ones. The most we bought was a disappointing schnitzel sandwich on a soft bun with Swiss cheese and kraut and red potatoes as the side.  Not very authentic. 
For the 6 hours on the road, and 2 -3 hours in the village, I would suggest skipping this tour and save your money.

itemListElement.name: Georgetown Neighborhood and Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky and beautiful!

name: Georgetown Neighborhood and Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky and beautiful!
description:
This tour highlights a neighborhood filled with art and historic architecture most travelers miss when they visit, and it's a very unique slice of old Seattle that still survives. It's a time machine! After we explore Georgetown, we will visit the heart of West Seattle, aka "The Junction" to visit the best record store in the city and soak up the charm. Then we're off to Alki Beach, a local favorite with great people watching, stunning views of Elliott Bay, Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. We may even spot a sea lion, a harbor porpoise, an eagle or an Orca on Alki, you never know. These are the places I take my friends and family when they visit, I'd like to share them with you.

With a max of 3 people,this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local! For a private version of this tour (1 to 4 people) please call/text 206-717-5797.

review.name: Georgetown, West Seattle and Alki beach which are hidden places to the tourists!!
review.reviewBody: It was second time I had a tour with Lynn. I had great time in capitol hills so I chose this tour again. Had fantastic time in George town and West Seattle. Those places are hidden ones that tourist do not know well. After I had the tours, I learned a lot about the history of this area and my travel to Seattle became more meaningful. Thank you Lynn and Mr. and Mrs. Plombon from Texas who had tour with me. These two tours are the fantastic moments of my trips in Seattle.

review.name: I'd book again in an instant!
review.reviewBody: Lynn was personally fabulous and professionally? The breadth of her enthusiastic knowledge was very impressive -- anything from advice on great food to shipping on the waterways to the history of architecture to where to get yummy chocolate. You name it, she knew it. Fun, engaging -- right on time (one of my personal favs...) and was obviously greeted in a warm manner by the people she introduced us to. I'd book this again no hesitation. Wonderful way to spend an afternoon and get to know the heart of a city. My 25 year-old loved it and so did we!

itemListElement.name: Lake, Old Growth Trees and Columbia City: Beautiful Natural Spaces and History

name: Lake, Old Growth Trees and Columbia City: Beautiful Natural Spaces and History
description:
Believe it or not, there is an old-growth forest in Seattle! We start at my favorite viewpoint in the city, perfect for your Instagram feed. Then we cruise the scenic shores of Lake Washington and learn the incredible history of how it was “re-plumbed” while on our way to Seward Park for fantastic views of Mt. Rainier (if the mountain is out!). This park is an incredible gem holding one of only 2 old-growth stands left in the city. The trail through the old-growth is flat, less than 1 mile long and it’s ‘flip-flop accessible’ We can walk as much or as little as you like. After that, let's get coffee in the beautiful, historic Columbia City neighborhood. This tour is mostly on foot, so wear your comfy shoes and appropriate weather gear. 

With a max of 3 people, this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see, places I take my friends and family when they visit! For a private version (1 to 4 people) please call/text 206-717-5797

review.name: Best Hidden Gems in Seattle
review.reviewBody: This is an AMAZING tour. Lynn is very knowledgeable about the history of this town and shows you all the hidden gems that Seattle has to offer. You get the personal VIP feel on this tour. Differently will do It again!

review.name: Seattle is a beautiful city and this tour shows first hand the true beauty of the outdoor spaces that are Seattle.
review.reviewBody: The Lake, Old growth trees and beach tour was a lot fun and very interesting.  Lynn, our tour guide, did a wonderful job talking about the history of the places we visited.  We took an easy hike through a beautiful park on Lake Washington with Douglas Firs over 700 years old. The beach was beautiful.  I would highly recommend this tour for anyone who enjoys being outdoors and learning about some cool history of Seattle.

review.name: Definitely worth the money!
review.reviewBody: My friend and I did this tour, and we absolutely loved it. We met her for coffee in the morning, and then off we went on the tour! She was so knowledgable and friendly, and she was also very open to what we wanted to do (even it was a little off-script). She packed a lovely little snack of home-brewed tea, local cheese, crackers, nuts, and fruit. I would definitely do another one her of tours!

review.name: A true locals tour!!!
review.reviewBody:
Lynn was awesome!!!  Absolutely awesome!  We had a great 3 hour tour!  Lynn was prompt, on time, and we had a great experience.  It was fun to see the neighborhoods of Seattle, take a walk in the old growth forest, see the shores of Lake Washington and Pudget Sound.  In between we were given golden nuggets of information to be used that day as well as throughout our stay.  
We took her advice to use the ferry to see the sound, go to Bainbridge Island and do so for just over $8 per ticket.  We had a great time.  In addition, Lynn provided us cold bottled water, homemade ice tea (my wife loved it) and we had a local fruit and cheese stash while sitting on the beach and watching for otters and whales.  Could not give Lynn enough 5 stars!!!!

review.name: Nature walk Galore!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I thoroughly enjoyed our tour with Lynn.  She was punctual, knowledgeable,  and her car was immaculate.  Not only did we visit parts of Seattle we would never have seen on our own, we learned so much about the history of the city.  She was so accommodating that she even directed us toward an awesome chocolate shop, which was not "officially on our itinerary!":)  I highly recommend this enriching experience; and this particular tour would be great for kids as well.

review.name: Lake, Old Growth Trees und die Beach Tour
review.reviewBody:
If you like quite private tours with only a few People you should do a tour with Lynn. As she is a native Seattle citizen for around 30 years she knows a lot about this city and its inhabitants. She explains everything in a very friendly, entertaining way and has a comprehensive knowledge of the city and places, that sweeping tourists are unlikely to see. On these tours (Lake, Old Growth Trees and Beach Tour) you may get to learn Seattle and nature surrounding Seattle. Together with Lynn we walked along Seattle Beach, had a typical American pick nick there, saw old trees, stones, Blue Herons, seals, hummingbirds and took a lot of amazing nature photos. 
But the park with really high and old trees is amazing with moss and ferns everywhere. So if you are interested in both, the city of Seattle and surrounding nature your first choice should be a tour of Seattle under the Radar with Lynn. 
Thank you Lynn for your patience while we taking so many pictures.

K. and H.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Neighborhoods 101 Tour: great for building a mental map of the city!

name: Seattle Neighborhoods 101 Tour: great for building a mental map of the city!
description: Each neighborhood in Seattle has a unique feel, architectural style and social scene. Let’s take a ride and explore some of them! We will check out Capitol Hill, center of nightlife, meander through the Volunteer Park neighborhood to see some of Seattle’s beautiful old Victorian-style homes, then we're off to Columbia City, Beacon Hill, and Georgetown. There are spectacular views all through this drive! If you’re a new resident of Seattle, or considering moving here, this is a great tour for you to start building a mental map of the feel of the city, guided by a resident of 30 years. For a private version of this tour (1 to 4 people) please call/text

review.name: Comprehensive tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Lynn was exceptional! She was punctual, courteous, informative, interesting, and comprehensive! We love her personality,too.She drove us through 4 neighborhoods and we got it and walked a bit so we could go in interesting spots. Along the way she covered any questions/topics that we posed.

review.name: Great Introduction to Seattle!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Lynn was phenomenal. She is incredibly knowledgeable about the city, from the architecture to the history of housing development to the old growth forest, not to mention food and entertainment. Her passion for the city is contagious. Don't miss this one!

review.name: Discovering a different Seattle
review.reviewBody:
Lynn's incites to all of Seattle were fantastic. She took us to areas not on the normal discover Seattle tour. We saw areas that we would have know about it.
She is informed, funny, and certainly loves her city.
Karen & Paul
NYC

review.name: Great option for those who are visiting Seattle
review.reviewBody: This one feels more like a private tour, which is great. Lynn is a very energetic and fun guide and she will take you to the interesting local neighborhoods for  history and cultural lessons. Expect to walk a little, but you will also get a chance to take photos from the car. We would definitely recommend this one if you are visiting Seattle. It will give you some insights on the local vibes and it will feel like you are hanging out with your auntie/cousin who is showing you around. The tour is about 3h. Great experience.

review.name: Best Seattle Tour!!
review.reviewBody: Absolutely the best - starting with the coffee!  Unlike the typical “get on the bus, drive by the usual sites”, Lynn takes you to the most interesting spots you wouldn’t find for yourself or with anyone else.  Fun, great information, accommodating - highly, highly recommend this tour!!

review.name: Terrific insider view of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Lynn's tour is a great way to see Seattle through the eyes of a local.  My tour was in mid September with two other passengers.  Lynn suggested neighborhoods that were at the top of my list.  We got a flavor for each neighborhood, and learned how populations had shifted over the years and changed some of the places.  I enjoyed seeing the longtime favorite locales, especially in Capitol Hill.  Lynn went above and beyond expectations, and even squeezed in a visit to Gas Works Park.  I definitely recommend Lynn's tour.

review.name: A great place and a beautiful environment with amazing foods and lovely staffs.It is very amazing and enjoyable , very ❤
review.reviewBody: The views is amazing.You can take a great and amazing photos in a beautiful environment.Great, great 👍

review.name: The absolute best tour of Seattle!!
review.reviewBody: Absolutely the best tour we could have asked for of Seattle. Lynn loves this city, and she will transmit her affection for it over the course of her informative and generous tour. Cannot recommend highly enough!!

review.name: Great tour by car with a local!
review.reviewBody: Lynn was a great guide and really knew her way around the city. Lots of interesting information about a few different neighborhoods and spots that we never would have found on our own. Would recommend taking this tour early in your trip so you know some cool places to go!

review.name: Fun & Informative Neighborhood Tour
review.reviewBody:
I took the 101 Seattle Neighborhoods tour with Lynn. She was personable and fun. We did a bit of walking and driving around. She is very passionate about the neighborhoods of Seattle and shared a lot about their histories and what makes each unique. Capitol Hill, Queen Anne, Fremont, West Lake, South Lake, Gaslight Park
It was a good introduction and overview of Seattle.

itemListElement.name: West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!

name: West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!
description: West Seattle is the spit of land you can see when gazing west from downtown Seattle and Pike Place Market. It’s hard to imagine, but west Seattle has beaches and lovely little shops along the waterfront with views of Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. Home to the best record store in the city where Pearl Jam once played and one of the last stands of old growth trees in Seattle, West Seattle is a world unto itself. The city skyline view is iconic from "the west side", perfect for photos to make your friends back home wish they were with us! These are the places I bring my friends and family when they visit. With a max of 3 people, this is a very personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores a part of the city that most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local! For a private version of this tour (1 to 4 people) please call/text

review.name: Bucket List Tour
review.reviewBody: The best tour of our trip because of Lynn. She texted her pic before the tour so we started out with comfort. She asked about us to customize our experience. It was the perfect start because I really wanted to see grunge-related places and she was excited to exceed my expectations. Lynn is super smart and shared knowledge that was relevant and interesting. I loved every stop including the quick stops for fantastic pics. Easy Street Records was a must-do and she pointed out so many more cool things that I would have missed. She allowed time for my purchases and for an ice cream. We had a yummy snack at Lincoln Park and we ended the day strolling in Alki Beach. Highly recommend Lynn and this tour.

review.name: THE BEST Neighborhood Tour - BY FAR
review.reviewBody:
When I initially met up with owner/guide Lynn Curtis, I didn't know what to expect, but man, did I get the best shock ever.  

We met at a local coffee shop and I was able to sample some of Seattle's best kept secret.  Starbucks isn't the only good coffee.  My cappuccino with a shot a hazelnut was not over frothy, but perfect, smooth and delicious.  After a few minutes of chit-chat, Lynn took me on a worldwide tour of West Seattle.  I learned so much and her time and attention to detail is the absolute best.  Lynn is passionate about Seattle and it comes through again and again with each tidbit of information she shares with you.  When I told her that I am looking to possibly move to Seattle in a few years, she offered a ton of suggestions and I knew that I had to return, just to sign up for more of her tours.  And just when I thought it was over, she took me to this fabulous Seattle based chocolatier, where all of my will power went out the window and I loaded up on the good stuff.  After a day with Lynn, you will come to truly love and embrace the city of Seattle. 

Hopping on a bus with other strangers is not a bad idea.  I did it, however, if you want an up close and personal, intimate touch, then I strongly encourage you to check out Lynn Curtis.  I know that I will reach out to her again!!!!

itemListElement.name: Roll the Dice Tour: Throw caution to the wind, dealer's choice tour!

name: Roll the Dice Tour: Throw caution to the wind, dealer's choice tour!
description:
On any given day in Seattle, there are experiences to be had that cannot be scheduled…

Maybe its a super windy day, a rare and perfect time for visiting the Sound Garden! Perhaps the resident orcas will decide to swim in Elliott Bay, so lets go see them. Maybe Jeff B. is having a BBQ at the beach house, so let’s hop a ferry and head west for a few hours! 

This tour is a dealer’s choice tour for a max of 4 people (only 1 ticket needed for up to 4 guests), where you allow me to host a personalized “best of the day” adventure. (There is no actual gambling on this tour :-) You can tell me what you are interested in doing, and I’ll craft a fun outing for us. 

NOTE: I chose Capitol Hill as a step on the tour, but the rest of the tour could be anywhere!

review.name: Family afternoon fun in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Our "Dealer's Choice" tour with Lynn was phenomenal. She is clearly passionate about and knowledgeable in the Seattle area. She was up to speed on local events happening the day of our tour to include a stop at Ballard Locks Fish Ladder where the king salmon were abundant and amazing to observe. We communicated in advance to share our family members' individual interests, and she tailored the tour to accommodate. For example, our daughters (ages 10 and 8) love to read and she took us to a fantastic book store. Highly recommend.

review.name: Fun and educational personalized tour with Lynn for the entire family
review.reviewBody:
My wife, my two teenage daughters, and me booked a private tour with Lynn on Nov 22. It far surpassed our expectations. We had told her in advance we liked the waterfront, history (including the present), and architecture. After communicating with us ahead of the tour, she arrived at our hotel on time. She had lovingly prepared an itinerary for us that took us through the city. We saw the house boats, Gasworks Park, Kerry Park, the area around Pike Street, and many more interesting sights and parts of the city. There was time to step into the famous Elliot Bay bookstore, too. It was a very fun and educational experience for my daughters.
Ask her to tell you about seeing Alice in Chains in her dorm basement! Highly recommended.

review.name: One of the best tours I've ever done
review.reviewBody: Lynn is an absolute treasure, enthusiastic and knowledgeable about the city and its history. We went through Pioneer Square, West Seattle, Alki Beach and Georgetown, stopping for drinks and lunch along the way. The absolute best kind of tour, getting to know the best of the city from a local who lives and loves it. Lynn was even kind enough to ferry me between my accommodations at the end of the tour!

itemListElement.name: Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, nightlife, history and attitude!

name: Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, nightlife, history and attitude!
description:
Center of Seattle’s LGBTQ community for years, "the hill" is vibrant, inclusive and delights with small independent shops, booming nightlife and attitude. We will learn about it's history and visit one of Seattle’s oldest parks with great views of the Space Needle. Along the way, we will check out a few of Seattle’s best book stores, some great record shops, sample locally made ice cream and confections, enjoy the best espresso in the city (in my opinion!) and see some of the most famous bars and live music venues in the city. This is a great way to plan your weekend agenda while in town if nightlife is your thing. These are the places I take my friends and family when they visit, I'd like to share them with you.

With a max of 3 people, this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local! For a private version of this tour (1 to 4 people) please call/text

review.name: Awesome tour!!
review.reviewBody: On our trip in Seattle we wanted to take a different tour that we had not already done. We chose to take the Capitol Hill tour with Lynn and oh my goodness are we glad that we did. She is such a wonderful tour guide and extremely knowledgeable on everything Seattle. I would love to just sit down with her and hear all of her stories from living in the city. She is such a fun person to be around and I highly recommend this tour if you love Seattle and want to learn more about the wonderful city and its history!

review.name: had a excellent Capitol hill tour with Lynn
review.reviewBody:
excellent excellent tour! Lynn is fantastic guide and this tour was amazing. Thank God I happened to find this tour. Lynn is history major and knows a lot about the history of Capitol Hill and all the stories about the buildings, stores, pretty houses and all other events in this area. I learned a lot about the real culture of people in Capitol Hills~! 
I just made reservation for Lynn's another tour in Georgetown and Alki beach. I am excited to have another great tour tomorrow. I wish more people (including many Koreans) also come and join this tour to know better about the towns.

review.name: A big win with Lynn!
review.reviewBody: The tour and Lynn (the owner) were great! It was like visiting an old friend who knew a lot about the city. We saw a lot of things we would have never found on our own. She knew a lot of history about the Capitol Hill neighborhood and experienced its many changes. Very down to earth. Coffee and water were a nice touch as well as the narwhal balls at The Unicorn. Would definitely book a tour with her again! Fun and relaxing experience.

review.name: Lynn is awesome!
review.reviewBody: Layne was a fabulous tour guide and we had such a fun time with her. She loves the city and helps you fall in love with it too by showing you all the funky, fun, and beautiful sites in Seattle.￼

review.name: Such an amazing time!!!
review.reviewBody: I went on the Capitol Hill tour with Lynn and I have to say Wowza this girl knows what's up! I picked that tour because I used to live on Capitol Hill, but my boyfriend had never experienced it. Well I soon realized on the tour that neither had I! She immediately brought us to Vivace, which I was very familiar with, but she recommended a drink that I have never heard of, which is now a drink that makes me want to go back to Capitol Hill! Then she brought us all over different areas that I never thought to go and showed me an amazing history that I never knew. Then we went to some of the local bars, but still she schooled me with really cool facts that I never would have known! Seriously the most amazing tour, that I thought was just going to be for my boyfriend. I highly recommend!!!

review.name: Wonderful Tour
review.reviewBody: Capitol Hill tour was great!  Lynn knows so much about this I learned about awesome (diamond in the rough) places there that I had not visited before even though I had lived on the Hill for for 13 years.  Even the places I had been before I got to see through new eyes due to the inclusion of history about the places we visited.  The whole tour was relaxed but not too slow, and I loved that we got to ask so many questions due to the small tour size.  An excellent experience and I can't wait to go on other tours to learn more about the city I already love!

itemListElement.name: From Seattle: Private Seattle City Tour

name: From Seattle: Private Seattle City Tour
description: Explore Seattle at your own pace on this private & professionally-guided City Tour. The tour begins from your hotel, where your personal local expert will pick your party up in a Pearl Chevrolet Suburban LTZ. From there, sit back and relax while your guide follows a 50-mile, 7 neighborhood route of the best sites in Seattle. Comfortably take in sites from T-Mobile Park to the Fremont Troll on this 3-hour tour. Scheduled stops include Pioneer Square, the Ballard Locks and Kerry Park, unless otherwise requested. Tour includes history and short photo opportunities at Pike Place Market and the Space Needle. Special requests granted when possible. Luggage not included in rate.

review.name: Interesting Tour of Seattle in 3 hours
review.reviewBody: Driver was polite, interesting, accommodating and a safe driver.  She picked out good places to visit and taught me lots about Seattle.

review.name: We would highly recommend this tour
review.reviewBody: Brian was fantastic! He was very knowledgeable and he gave us a great tour. The best thing about private tours is that you can customize it any way you want it.

review.name: Fantastic tour
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour to see the most of Seattle.  Our guide, Carl, was fantastic - local with great knowledge of the area and hidden gems.  Thank you!

review.name: Highly recommend!  ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
review.reviewBody: Our private guide was very knowledgeable about the history of the city of Seattle.  He was also a great driver.  Highly recommend!

review.name: Great way to know Seattle on your way
review.reviewBody: Tyler was such a friendly guide to show me all the spots I requested. I'm so delighted with the time he dedicate to me, and I would definitely would repeat the experience and recomend to others.

review.name: Fantastic! Do it!!
review.reviewBody: What a fantastic tour!!! Amazing in every way. But the best part was our tour guide and driver Erica. She showed us everything, she's as nice as she can be, we could not have asked for more. Thank you Erica! I hope you see this! You made our Seattle trip perfect!

review.name: City Tour
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful experience from start to finish. Tiz in the office could not have been nicer or more helpful. Tyler was great! Knowledgeable, friendly, informative. Listened to our needs and was a pleasure to have as a guide. Could not have had a better experience.

review.name: Definitely worth it! Highly recommend for all ages!
review.reviewBody: Our guide, Jeff, was fantastic! Our family of 4 (inc. a 9 and 12 year old) had a great experience! Jeff took us to a number of places in and around Seattle, sharing interesting info and answering all sorts of questions. It’s a great way to see and learn about the city- definitely worth it. Highly recommend!!

review.name: Very Nice!
review.reviewBody: John was excellent. Very friendly. Showed us some nice sites of Seattle. Views were fantastic. Highly recommend this tour.

review.name: Seattle's best sights all covered with a great guide / chauffeur !
review.reviewBody: From the first meeting with Bryan D. we KNEW this was going to be a great tour. Knowledgeable about the city, the history and the region, we had the best tour en famille we have ever had. Comfortable vehicle. Safe driver, very attentive to our questions ( of which there were many!). To see Seattle from the perspective of a local professional guide (Bryan has been doing this for over 14 years ...his skill is evident !) was worth every penny. In our time together we toured all the major areas and neighborhoods in with great detail and to the "characters" that built Seattle's industries and technologies. Viewing the city from many vista outlook areas gave the true perspective on the lay of the land. From Pike's Market area, through the business centers to the glorious residential areas to the port areas, we now understand the magic that Seattle holds for the citizens. For anyone taking a vacation here or a cruise from the port, THIS tour is THE tour to reserve. Customized to whatever wants to see that come up during our conversations. "Let me show you that area" was the credo. Yes, Bryan has his sights he wishes to ensure we see, but he went out of his way for a couple mystical areas like t6he floating homes ( and floating bridges) and the lakes areas. Thank you Bryan D. for a day to remember and nan education about your fine city. Bravo! Highly recommended. A MUST do tour ...  "fer sure eh" as we might say as Canadian guests ! Merci beaucoup de Montreal to Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Visit Snoqualmie Falls and Hike to Twin Falls

name: Visit Snoqualmie Falls and Hike to Twin Falls
description: This tour involve a 2 miles of of hiking. We've had several different fitness levels complete the hike without issues. This is an experience for someone who is interested in enjoying the forest and waterfalls in the morning. The short trip includes ecological as well as cultural interpretation of the natural areas visited. It is a truly beautiful experience to be immersed in a temperate rainforest.

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: It was a great experience. Jonny was an excellent guide and explained each stop of the tour very well. I loved the views of the waterfalls. I highly recommend it.

review.name: Well worth it - great guide!
review.reviewBody: Information accurate. Johnny our guide was very patient and knowledgeable. Gave us water and patiently took photos for us in all the best spots. The falls were stunning. The hike was a little bit challenging for us but not unbearable! Well worth it!

review.name: Experience rain forest and beautiful falls
review.reviewBody: Hiking was fun and a bit challenging for me , muddy shoes . Beautiful rain forest and magnificent falls ! How delightful . Our guide John was very low key and personable and he kept company with the people in the group to feel included.

review.name: Taste of the wilderness outside Seattle
review.reviewBody: Beautiful falls, short hike in the forest, not far out of Seattle. Guide was helpful and informative. Great half day for out of town.

review.name: 10/10 experience
review.reviewBody: We had Jonny as a guide, he was great!! The hike was a unique experience and he was very informative and attentive to us. Would definitely recommend

review.name: Recommend Thjs Beautiful Tour!
review.reviewBody: My boyfriend and I went on thjs tour on our 5 day trip to Seattle a few days ago. Our guide was Jonny who was informative, kind, and overall a good guide for the tour. We broke a sweat on the hike itself but nothing crazy! Would recommend wearing good shoes for walking/hiking (we wore hiking shoes) to avoid trips or slips! Also would recommend wearing comfy clothes and avoiding jeans or anything that would be uncomfortable to break a bit of a sweat in! The waterfalls were gorgeous and the forest really was magnificent. We also liked getting to see some of the small towns we passed by while driving up towards the hike. We recommend this tour highly to anyone who wants to get a feel for the forest/nature of Washington outside of the city of Seattle itself!

review.name: Recommended tour!
review.reviewBody: Jonny was informative, friendly, and flexible.  We enjoyed our trip to the falls and the hike.  We highly recommend this 1/2 day tour.

review.name: Snoqualmie Falls and Twin Falls
review.reviewBody: Jonny was absolutely the best tour guide anyone could get. He was super flexible and one of our stops was an unfortunate situation so we all pivoted to another experience is was awesome. Thank you Jonny and don’t forget to tip!!!!!

review.name: Visit to Snoqualmie Falls
review.reviewBody: We absolutely loved this tour.  Beautiful, serene and as close to nature as can get.  We were surrounded by lush foliage, viewed wonderful waterfalls and hiking experience was terrific.  Our tour guide, Jonny, was great with pointing out sites of interest and took memorable photos that we will treasure for years to come.  Anyone who takes this tour will be pleased with his guidance attentiveness.

review.name: Beautiful views and awesome hike
review.reviewBody: Jonny was a great guide. He answered many questions and even helped out taking photos. He pointed out several things along the hike that we wouldn't have noticed on our own.  Great hike and a great way to spend half a day if you can fit it in!

name: Snoqualmie Falls, Experience the Wonder
description:
Snoqualmie Falls is visited by over 1.5 million people per year. At 268 ft ( 82 M ) tall, it is truly a brilliant natural wonder to behold and a 'Must-See' during your visit to Seattle! 

Skip the taxi / ride share service and join our small, adults-only group in a comfortable, clean van. Enjoy fresh, bottled water and the company of a friendly guide. Afterwards, we'll drop you off back at your hotel where you can then continue to enjoy the remainder of your evening. 
***Please note: 

This activity is strictly for adults ages 18 and older. Children under the age of 18 are not permitted - no exceptions. Pets are also not permitted out of respect for our travelers with allergies.

itemListElement.name: ALL-INCLUSIVE Day Hike, Dinner and Snoqualmie Falls!

name: ALL-INCLUSIVE Day Hike, Dinner and Snoqualmie Falls!
description:
Enjoy an exciting day hike to an Alpine Lake or Mountain Top with spectacular views and a friendly guide! Afterwards, we'll enjoy a traditional Seattle-Area, American Meal at a local restaurant before ending our day with a visit to World-Famous Snoqualmie Falls. 

Details:
-Hotel pickup included
-Small Group of 2-15 people
-Hike distance is 5-8 miles (8.1km - 13km) and includes hills / elevation gain
-Enjoy genuine American Food for Dinner at a highly-rated local restaurant or PUB
-Visit World-Famous Snoqualmie Falls where you can get some stunning photos
-Drop off back at your hotel when our adventures is complete

itemListElement.name: Mount Rainier Customized Tour from Seattle

name: Mount Rainier Customized Tour from Seattle
description:
Join a small group of fellow travelers and a friendly guide for a scenic drive through the Cascade Mountains, where you’ll marvel at the evergreen forests, a towering volcano that rises above the surrounding landscape, sparkling lakes, and historic towns along the way. Stop at scenic viewpoints and waterfalls as you capture breathtaking photos at picturesque viewpoints.
You’ll also have free time to explore the park’s trails, wildlife, and visitor center at your leisure. Whether you’re a nature lover, a history buff, or a thrill-seeker, you’ll find something to love about Mount Rainier at your own pace. Mount Rainier is more than just a mountain. It’s a national treasure that offers something for everyone.
This tour includes convenient pickup and drop-off from selected locations in downtown Seattle and airport hotels. Don’t miss this chance to see one of America’s most spectacular natural wonders. Book your Mount Rainier Tour from Seattle today and prepare for a memorable adventure!

review.name: Majestic! Long lasting memories in Washington state
review.reviewBody: Farshid was excellent! He is very knowledgeable of Seattle and Mount Rainier. We had an outstanding time he stopped at viewpoints so that we could take lots of pictures. He was very patient. He provided all the tools we needed to go for a little hike. I can say that the elevation did cause me to feel alittle sick . Farshid, was there to make sure that my medications were sufficient and if I needed any further assistance, he was able to help. I really appreciate the patience and understanding we were able to finish the trip. It was beautiful and well worth every dime. I will do it again when I come back to Seattle. thank you so much!

review.name: Great day with the family making memories.
review.reviewBody:
Great tour, Farshid was very professional and kind and took great care of our family of 5.
We had an amazing time and would highly recommend Oktaytours.
The weather was bad and we did not go to Mount Rainier but we went to Leavenworth , we saw the Snoqualmie Falls , we visited the ski resort and had a snowball fight and lots of other stips.

review.name: Slav was THE BEST.
review.reviewBody: Our trip to Mt. Rainier was breathtaking!!! We also toured the Starbucks corporate headquarters in the SoDo Neighborhood. Next, we visited Snoqualmie Falls. Then we traveled to North Bend to explore the Twin Peaks filming location and savor the iconic Cherry pie from the RR,  at the RR Twede’s  cafe. I cannot say enough about Slav.  He went so above and beyond for each of us.  He was very knowledgeable about so many plants and EVERYTHING.  Parts of our tour we could not do because of winter weather but Slav made sure he compensated us and we loved every second of the day.  Very special thanks to Slav.   Highest recommendation I can give.

review.name: Mount Rainier best tour
review.reviewBody: The tour to Mount Rainier is the best, with Farshid as an even better guide, excellent driver and guide, knows the place perfectly, knows the best photo spots, makes good stops, the view is spectacular the higher it gets each time beautiful, the photos don't do it justice, you have to do the tour, 100% recommended, then when we get off, Farshid tells us the story accompanied by a short walk through the forest, I feel happy to have done this tour.

review.name: When in Seattle, Don't miss Mount Rainier!
review.reviewBody:
Please read entirely.  Before our Alaskan Cruise from Seattle we wanted to see Mount Rainier.  We had booked with Oktaytours and the best decision we could have made. The cheapest choice is not always the best.   The owner Daniel had reached out to us because of cancelations that left just my wife and myself on the tour.  He said that he had other options but not the Mount Rainier as it was just the two of us.  As we told him that was really what we had our hearts set on that we would just look else where, he would not have that. He wanted us to see Mount Rainier.   We ended up with a personal tour by the owner himself and it could have not been better.  It was absolutely breathtaking and beautiful.  Never felt rushed and Daniel was always ready for photos and any needs we wanted.  After our cruise we had 1 additional day to explore Seattle so of course it was an easy choice to reach back out to Oktaytours.  We were picked up from the cruise port and after our Best of Seattle Tour that day, they dropped us off at the airport.  Special thanks to Vlad for a great tour.

The Martins

review.name: Terrific Day with Mt. Rainier
review.reviewBody: Our guide, Vladimir, was amazing.  Very personal, courteous and knowledgeable.  He was open to customizing our tour and made 9-10 stops with interpretive and historical knowledge.  Vlad allowed us as much time at each stop and we never felt rushed.  The tour included 2 other people who were also very friendly and willing to go with the flow.  Mt. Rainier is a very special place and deserves respect and admiration and Vladimir made sure our trip included as much time and awareness to get a full feeling of the majestic Mt. Rainier National Park.  Worth every penny!!!

name: Bite-Sized Seattle History & Food Tour
description:
The one and only tour of Seattle you'll ever need - in just 45 minutes! Explore the city's rich history, stopping by world-famous attractions and some hidden gems. We'll stretch our legs, do some food shopping in Pike Place Market - and build some uniquely Seattle snacks that showcase local cuisine and history!

Guests love this tour because...
1) We keep our group size small
2) We have folks in and out in 45 minutes
3) We eat awesome food you won't stumble across on your own
4) Our guides love sharing local recommendations! Want to know where to get sushi? Where to grab a drink? How to get from A to B? We got you.

My goal is that at the end of the tour you will not only see some beautiful sites, but also understand how all that history shaped Seattle into the city it is today. This is the most fun "lunch & learn" you've ever attended!

review.name: Recommend this tour in Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody: Awesome tour! Really great if you’re short on time and want to learn A TON about Seattle in an hour! The tour guide was engaged, offered us water and even a printed list of city recommendations that were so helpful!

review.name: We highly recommend this tasty and informative tour!
review.reviewBody: My family and I did the bite sized Seattle history & food tour with Aidan yesterday and had a wonderful time! Aiden is very friendly and knowledgeable. He showed us hidden gems and places we would have never known about otherwise. We enjoyed delicious food including smoked salmon and seasonal fruit. We would highly recommend his tour to anyone looking for a fun Seattle experience!

review.name: Perfect for locals and visitors alike!
review.reviewBody: What a great tour!! Lots of great local knowledge fit into a conveniently short time frame. The highlight was the locally sourced snack at the end.

review.name: Perfect start to a long weekend
review.reviewBody: This was the best way to start our long weekend trip in Seattle. It gave us the lay of the land plus tidbits of trivia and history we wouldn’t have gotten in our own. I highly recommend this tour with Aidan.

review.name: Seattle Fun
review.reviewBody: The tour guide gave good knowledge nuggets of Seattle and the lunch that was provided was amazing. The weather was perfect when we went and made the experience a loot more enjoyable

review.name: Tasty tour!
review.reviewBody: As someone who has lived in Seattle all my life, I can easily say this is a great tour for first time visitors! Even for residents of the area, you're still bound to enjoy yourself or learn a fun fact about the city that you weren't yet aware of. Aidan is an absolutely enthusiastic host who is more than happy to answer your questions. The food, especially the smoked salmon, was delicious! Highly recommend!

review.name: Informative local tour!
review.reviewBody: Very informative and fun local tour of the Pike Place area! Aidan provided great context to history in the area and the smoked salmon bite was to die for! Highly recommend this experience!

review.name: Fun Seattle tour guide!
review.reviewBody: Fun experience!! Quick and efficient dip into Seattle culture with a lot of good information presented! Guide is very knowledgable and keeps the tour moving, also some smoked salmon as a treat at the end was a cherry on top!

review.name: Great walk with some candied salmon
review.reviewBody: Did an hour long history tour with Aidan. Great intro to the history, even as a local. Had some awesome candied salmon and bread for an intro to the food. Loved it.

review.name: Everything I expected!
review.reviewBody: Aidan was great, enjoyed all the history he shared about this beautiful city. Always wanted to travel to Seattle.
